## Platform caps + floor (canonical YAML)

- **Stowed path (Cursor):** **`~/.cursor/configurations/orchestration-policies/subagent-caps.yml`**
- **DotMate source:** **`ai/cursor/tech-team/configurations/orchestration-policies/subagent-caps.yml`**
- **Contains:** per-**`platforms`** max concurrent sub-agents, depth, session totals; global **`floor`** (default min **6**, target **8**, half-floor **3**); **`defaults`** (parallel-first, serial justification, **`fan_out_minimum`**); **`coordinator_overrides`** for **`remotion-builder`** and **`n8n-builder`** (**min** **4**, **target** **6**).
- Coordinators **MUST** load caps **before** planning waves; if the active platform’s **`max_concurrent_subagents`** is **less than** the YAML **`floor.min_subagents_per_coordinator`**, use **batched waves** (dispatch up to cap, await completion, dispatch next wave) per **`parallel-dispatch`** until the effective tree meets policy — log **`platform_cap_hit`** + wave plan in **`below_floor_justification`** when a **single** wave cannot satisfy floor alone.

